==Wikipedia dump==
'''Zulma''' is a feminine given name.  Some say it comes from the [[Wikipedia:Arabic language|Arabic]] word ''Suleiman''. The name is very typical in [[Wikipedia:Latin America]] because of an [[Wikipedia:Argentina|Argentine]] actress named [http://chumis.tripod.com/zulmafaiad/ Zulma Faiad] who toured Latin America in the [[Wikipedia:1970s]]. Many people heard of this name and thought of it as a great baby name.

In [[Wikipedia:Spanish language|Spanish]], the letter ''Z'' is pronounced like the [[Wikipedia:English language|English]] "th" in most parts of [[Wikipedia:Spain]], and like English "s" in Latin America, where the name is therefore pronounced [[Wikipedia:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] {{Wikipedia:IPA|/'sulma/}}